des:
The Perenio Lite allows you to control such devices using voice commands:
- Power Link Smart Socket;
- IR Remote Control.

For voice control of the Power Link Smart Socket, you must purchase the PEACG01 Smart Home Control Center. 

How to Set up the Perenio Power Link Smart Socket and IR Remote Control
1. Download the app "Perenio Smart: Building Management System" from the Play Market or App Store.
2. Register a Perenio account.
3. Purchase one of the Perenio IoT devices that is controlled via Alice (for example, a Power Link Smart Socket, an IR Remote Control).
4. Click on the "Merge accounts" button at the bottom.
5. Enter Your username and password from the account Perenio.
6. Click on the "Update device list" button at the bottom.
7. Click on the "Go to device List" button.
8. Choose a Smart Socket or an IR Remote Control.
9. Add the name of the device and zone in Russian language (for example, "Collider" and " Nuclear Reactor")

How to use the Perenio Power Link Smart Socket?
1) Connection to an electric heated towel rail;
2) Remote reboot of devices (on/off, such as PC);
3) Turn on the backlight for flowers/flowerpots/planters;
4) Remote turn on/off the heater;
5) Connection to a coffee machine (warm-up), slow cooker, grill/free-standing oven
6) Turn off the charging of your phone or other equipment at night;
7) Remote control of the humidifier/air washer;
8) Remote control of hair irons/curling irons;
9) Control (disable) game consoles (TVs) for children;
10) Make it easier to turn off or on the devices that are connected to hard-to-reach outlets (under the table, behind the cabinet);
11) Install a video surveillance camera to turn it off at a certain time for privacy (when you are at home or at a certain time);
12) Turn on and off the aquarium light.

How to use the IR Remote Control?
1) Turn on or off a specific device.
2) Turn on or off the device with a non-unique name with location clarification.
3) Enable or disable a group of devices of the same type/group of devices.
4) Control of the TV.
5) Turn the TV on or off.
